The paper presents a data structure for maintaining information about bridges in a graph, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and graph algorithms. The paper uses techniques from dynamic graph algorithms and combinatorics, which are typically studied in the computer science subfields of data structures (cs.DS), computational geometry (cs.CG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
